divs: Sighting DetailsWas driving west on route 64 just east of Oregon,Illinois about 7:30pm.Caught the movement of this object as it traveled south at about 160-180 mph.Was overcast, no direct sunlight...cloudy.This object was only viewable because of it's outline...it was the same color as the sky...like I was looking through it as if it was made of glass.Was probably 1000ft-1500ft west of me....about 600ft-800ft above power lines...just high enough to see over the treeline(hilly terrain).watched it move south for about 5-6 seconds before I lost it in the treeline.The scary part for me is....I don't think you could see something like that on a clear sun filled day...I could only see the edge of it...the outline as it moved...if it were still...I don't think i would have seen it.The edge that I could see was hazy...like heat shimmer off of pavement..but much more intense.Was as large as a 80-100 feet from edge to edge and about 30 feet from top to bottom.
Summary: Nearly invisible oval shaped object traveling over power lines.
